title Oobium Routing from the Outside In

p This guide covers the user-facing features of Rails routing. By referring to this guide, you will be able to:
ul.intro
	li Understand the code in Activator#addRoutes
	li Construct your own routes, using either the preferred resourceful style or with the match method
	li Identify what parameters to expect an action to receive
	li Automatically create paths and URLs using route helpers
	li Use advanced techniques such as constraints and Rack endpoints